Subject: Re: [T2] Saving radio settings

On Wed, 16 Jul 2003, Ted Finesman wrote:

> Hi Volks- Can anyone suggest a way to keep my radio settings when I
> disconnect the battery?  I disconnect my battery every time I work on my bus
> and I generally forget to reset the radio until I am on my way out of
> town..... Ted (financial report coming- fund drive was a great success)

You can use a 9V battery to keep the radio alive, but you have to put a
series diode in the circuit so you can hook the little battery up to the
cables (alligator clips are good for this) without blowing it up.

George
